(250, 1, '2014-01-14 07:22:20', '2014-01-14 07:22:20', '<h3>Welcome to the 2013 Bradford Ribfest!</h3>\r\nBradford deserved a Ribfest.  So, a group of Volunteers led by Rick Brooks decided to put one on. All proceeds will go towards Community Charity.<a title="CLICK HERE TO VOLUNTEER" href="http://eepurl.com/EKuX5" target="_blank"><img class="alignright" alt="volunteers" src="http://bradfordribfest.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/volunteers.png" width="292" height="187" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis September 20th weekend, join us to celebrate community, and of course, some great Ribs. Enjoy the <a title="KIDSZONE" href="http://bradfordribfest.ca/kidszone-2/">Midway</a>, <a title="KidsZone" href="http://bradfordribfest.ca/kidszone/">KidsZone</a>, Live Entertainment and more in our inaugural Ribfest!\r\n\r\nWe welcome folks from everywhere this weekend, as Bradford grows, so does our Hospitality!\r\n\r\nTo keep up to date, make sure to Like us on Facebook or Follow Us on Twitter.  And don’t forget to enter our contests!  A special shout-out goes to <a title="Platinum Sponsor" href="http://bradfordribfest.ca/platinum-sponsor/">Zehrs</a> for letting us use their property and excellent help with this event!\r\n<h3>Safety</h3>\r\nWe want your time at Bradford Ribfest to be fun and safe. If you can Bike, Walk, or Car Pool, this will help with congestion around the grounds and parking lots.\r\n\r\nPlease, NO DOGS or PETS are allowed. There will be a first aid station available. Absolutely NO outside food or drinks will be permitted on the grounds.\r\n<h3>Our Volunteers</h3>\r\nWow – it wasn’t a lot of time to prepare fo a RibFest, but we did it! We will be out and about helping out all weekend, so make sure you stop and say HI. A special thank you to everyone who has worked so hard in the planning and preparation for this great event. These folks are terrific.\r\n\r\nGeneral inquiries: <a title="mailto:bwgribfest@gmail.com" href="mailto:bwgribfest@gmail.com">bwgribfest@gmail.com\r\n</a>Volunteer inquiries: <a title="mailto:volunteers.bwgribfest@gmail.com" href="mailto:volunteers.bwgribfest@gmail.com">volunteers.bwgribfest@gmail.com</a>\r\n\r\nSee ya soon!\r\n\r\nRick Brooks', 'Sponsors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '224-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-14 07:22:20', '2014-01-14 07:22:20', '', 224, 'http://www.bradfordlicious.com//?p=250', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(255, 1, '2014-01-14 07:46:00', '2014-01-14 07:46:00', '<h3>Welcome to Bradfordlicious Festivals!</h3>\r\nGet ready Bradford to enjoy delicious eats from a variety of worldwide culinary offerings from over 20 restaurants this February 1<sup>st</sup> to February 28<sup>th</sup>, 2014 as the Inaugural Bradfordlicious Festival sets the stage to be a great annual event.<a href="http://www.bradfordlicious.com//wp-content/uploads/2013/12/food-1261446_93935398.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-254 alignright" alt="food-1261446_93935398" src="http://www.bradfordlicious.com//wp-content/uploads/2013/12/food-1261446_93935398.jpg" width="730" height="487" /></a>\r\n\r\nRestaurant-goers will get a chance to give up their favourite restaurants to try new tastes from around the world for an unbeatable price at just $20 for a 3-course dinner and $10 for a 3-course lunch.\r\n\r\nThe 2014 Bradfordlicious event will be a fundraising endeavour in support of helping local charities, and we are looking for it to become an annual fundraiser to support local children in need. Our intention is to not only help our local charities but to make a significant difference in the community.\r\n\r\nBy inviting all residents of the Town of Bradford, and expanding our promotion and awareness to our surrounding community neighbours, we hope to help generate awareness for the charity we are supporting as well as for Bradford Businesses. By causing an increase in activity into our town, we are allowing Bradford Businesses to put themselves on display to travellers that may not have otherwise known about them.\r\n\r\n<i>Three Course Dinner Menu is to be chosen from a select menu at each restaurant. Price does not include applicable taxes, alcohol or additional menu items. Please contact the restaurants in advance for reservations. Ask about select menu.</i>\r\n<strong>General inquiries: </strong><a href="mailto:bradfordlicious@gmail.com"><strong>bradfordlicious@gmail.com</strong></a>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-14 07:46:00', '2014-01-14 07:46:00', '', 22, 'http://www.bradfordlicious.com//?p=255', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
